<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Scuby</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Do people think that Improved Healing III items are worthwhile for clerics?<P>I was lucky enough to have an Idol of the Underking gathering dust in the bank, so I've had a play with it.<P>Using Remedy and Divine Light, I found a range of effects from 0.87% extra to 20%.  The average came out about 12% from 34 casts.<P>I tend to use CE and CH most of the time, so the focus item is largely useless to me, which is why a druid friend tends to borrow it.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Boanerges</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Same arguments here as for Healing Gift and Adept. It benefits Remedy and those few times you use Divine Light and that's about it.<P>Would I go out of my way to buy or wear one? No.<BR>Would I like to have one?<BR>Yes.<P>------------------<BR>Boanerges Thundercry<BR>High Priest of Prexus<BR><A HREF="http://www.cohort.cc" TARGET=_blank>Cohort Chalybeius</A><BR>Cazic Thule Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Tabb</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">If this ability were on some of the already good high end cleric items...<P>White dragon sash<BR>Cloak of the Sky<P>etc...<P>then it would be a nice added ability for our class.<P>As is, however, it simply is NOT worth trading out items ... almost any other item... in the slots it comes in for the effect... which only effects 2 spells.<P>Obulous death shroud, however, is so good its worth banking your 8th shawl for almost.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"> thx 200 mana save on group buffing Blessing of Aegolism</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Pastor Skellbane</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Even an effect that is usefull to you, I don't think it is worth trading or buying items just yet, as there will be at least one more round of focus items added, and you may find out you spent xxk pp to get a focus effect that your existing equipment might get next time  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/frown.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Demeros</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Does healing 3 work on the group heals from your Velious quest legs? I could see that being handy if you were in a situation where you wanted to use them a lot.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Lala</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I believe item effects are exempted from focus items.    <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/frown.gif"><P><BR><P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=78916" TARGET=_blank>Aalamdara A'shani</A><BR><A HREF="http://www.darkblood.com" TARGET=_blank>Darkblood</A> <BR><I>Solusek Ro</I></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Seethur</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Actually healing gift is pretty damn good for the numerous ssra mobs that proc balance.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gello</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Wow thanks for posting this.  My slot most in need of upgrade was range: wearing sarnak prayer beads.  I happened to have this idol in my nec's bank.  I lose some minor stats/ac/15hp/mana, but more than made up for those with earring of the solstice today.<P>So far my highest DL is 1165 with healing adept 1.  That's almost 200hp over normal DL (971 w/HA1).  Highest critical is 2024.  For me it's a great tradeoff.  Granted, not as useful as damage 3 is to nukers, but it's nice.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>This will get annoying tho in knockback fights where I wear a supple scale armband for range (cazic itraer vyemm etc):<P> <IMG SRC="http://freeshell.org/~gello/DL.gif"> <P>With spell haste that'd be 6 lines of spam for casting one spell.  I forsee a filter for focus effects coming.<p>[This message has been edited by Gello (edited 06-11-2002).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Demeros</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>I believe item effects are exempted from focus items.<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>There seems to be some inconsistency on this point. My enchanter was getting buff duration focus on his Earring of Blazing Energy (casts a damage shield) but not on Speed of the Shissar.<P>Anyone know for sure if this focus works with the legs or not?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">JanSorensen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Rumor is they work if and only if the spell the item casts is a spell your class can normally cast.<P>Ie - Shissar isnt a normal chanter spell but the DS from the earring is.<P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4264" TARGET=_blank>Mikar of the Nexus</A><BR>High Priest of Brell<BR><A HREF="http://companions.windsofstorm.net/" TARGET=_blank>The Companions</A><BR>The Tribunal</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kaysha Soulsinger</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Spells and effects cast from items have a certain set level. Could it be that it only works when that level falls within the limits of the focus item?<P>------------------<BR>- Kaysha Soulsinger<BR>Templar in the 55th Circle of Erollisi Marr on Lanys T'Vyl<BR><I>The road to Heaven is paved with stones from Hell</I></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gello</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Like the rest of the focii, improved healing works with group CH:<P> <IMG SRC="http://freeshell.org/~gello/spamheal.gif"> <P>I've already been told I'm never allowed to fight Lcea again hehe</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Artemi</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Can anyone confirm if Improve Healing item works with our Celestial line of spells?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Cayleu</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Heh, I agree on obulous shroud and Mana preservation 3.<P>I was just awarded Sky Watcher's Monocle last night, so I can wear 8th shawl and still get the focus effect! : )<P>10% less mana used for buffs and on DL's rocks!</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
